---
import Footer from '@ui/components/atoms/Footer.astro'
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro'
---
<Base title="Methodology — SaferSkills">
  <main class="flex-1 px-6 py-16">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl prose">
      <h1>Methodology</h1>
      <p>
        SaferSkills is a public, free, Apache-2.0 trust-scoring service. Every
        detection rule is open; every score is reproducible; every verdict is
        appealable.
      </p>

      <h2>Inputs</h2>
      <p>A GitHub repository URL or, from W4, an <code>npx</code>-installable package name.</p>

      <h2>Detection categories</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Identity</strong> — author signature, GitHub org age, signing keys.</li>
        <li><strong>Integrity</strong> — file-hash drift, unsigned commits, content vs claimed version.</li>
        <li><strong>Behavior</strong> — shell RCE, prompt injection, tool poisoning, MCP rug-pull, hooks that disable monitoring.</li>
        <li><strong>Provenance</strong> — supply chain (dependencies, transitive risk), SBOM presence, build reproducibility.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Scoring model</h2>
      <p>
        <code>aggregate_score = 0.25 × identity + 0.25 × integrity + 0.30 × behavior + 0.20 × provenance</code>
      </p>
      <p>
        Each sub-score is 0–100, computed from per-rule penalties documented in
        each rule's RFC. Same input → same score. No model. No random seed. No
        temperature.
      </p>

      <h2>Reproducibility</h2>
      <p>
        Every report records <code>rubric_version</code> and
        <code>engine_version</code> Git SHAs plus the artifact's
        <code>inputs_hash</code>. Any vendor can re-derive any historical
        verdict.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitations</h2>
      <p>
        Every rule's RFC includes a "What this rule cannot catch" section. The
        rubric explicitly does not flag closed-source artifacts (they get a
        "Provenance: unscoped" badge, not a score).
      </p>

      <h2>Full reference</h2>
      <p>
        Authoritative documents are in the <a href="https://github.com/OpenLatch/saferskills/blob/main/docs/methodology.md">docs/methodology.md</a>,
        <a href="https://github.com/OpenLatch/saferskills/blob/main/docs/rules.md">docs/rules.md</a>, and the
        <a href="https://github.com/OpenLatch/saferskills/tree/main/rubric">rubric/</a> directory.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
